Asma Lamnawar (Arabic; a mụrụ n'abalị 25 ọnwa Julaị afọ 1978 na Casablanca, Morocco) bụ onye na-agụ egwu Moroccan. O mere abụ mbụ ya n'afọ 1995 na "Angham", emume nke Moroccan Radio na TV mepụtara, ebe ọ meriri ihe nrite maka ntụgharị kachasị mma, ọ bụ ezie na ọ na-egbu oge ịmalite ọrụ egwu ya ruo n'afọ 2002. O dekọrọ egwu maka ihe nkiri telivishọn na ihe nkiri Moroccan. Ọ gara njem na otu "Oriental Mood" na Denmark, Sweden na karịsịa na Egypt.

E wepụtara abọm mbụ ya, "ناري" ("Fiery"), n'afọ 2002. "شي عادي" ("Ihe Dị Mma") ka Art-Jazeera Saudi Arabia wepụtara n'afọ 2005, ya na Abu bụrụ abụ abụọ n'otu afọ ahụ. Ọ bịanyere aka na Rotana n'afọ 2008, wee wepụta abọm "من ና ና ና ና لبكره" ("Men Hina L Bukhra") n'otu afọ ahụ. E wepụtara abọm ọzọ (Rouh) na Rotana n'afọ 2010. Asma wepụtara abọm Sabiya, nke Rotana mepụtara, n'afọ 2017.
